data.title: American Legion: Frank, Meyer lead Malcolm to first-round win in Class C state tournament
data.meta_description: Maddox Meyer dominated the mound and Hayden Frank dominated the plate in a potent 1-2 punch for Malcolm on Saturday.
data.text:
Maddox Meyer dominated the mound and Hayden Frank dominated the plate in a potent 1-2 punch for Malcolm on Saturday.

The Clippers, looking to defend its Class C State title, opened the state tournament with a 6-0 victory over Imperial in Wakefield.

Meyer struck out 10 batters in 6 1/3 innings, while Frank doubled, tripled and drove in three runs in a 2-for-3 performance at the dish.

Frank cushioned Malcolm's 3-0 lead through six innings to 5-0 with a 2-RBI triple in the top of the seventh and added another run for good measure on Brixon Meyer RBI single.

Luke Schmidt and Garrett England added two hits each for the Clippers. England also scored three times.

Hickman 5, Wayne 2: Clutch hitting in the top of the sixth helped Hickman escape Wayne Saturday in the Class B opener for both teams in Holdrege. An RBI single from Jordan Monroe followed by a Crew Moeller double and Tanner Klein RBI groundout pushed Hickman's lead to 5-0. Wayne homered in the bottom half of the inning to cut into the deficit but the arms of Moeller and Kaden Kraft shut the door. Moeller struck out five in 5 1/3 innings, while Kraft retired five by strikeout in 1 2/3 innings.

Wahoo 3, Auburn 1: Jesse Stebbing went 5 1/3 innings and struck out four in a pitchers dual with Auburn's Travon Shaw. Wahoo, who trailed 1-0 through four innings, broke through against Shaw with two runs in the top of the fifth to take the lead for good.
